sting we standardize the service level across all events to simplify things.\n\nBut the case mentions that for these formal wedding events, we bring "nicer china" and have more interaction with attendees. Evans believes customers are paying a premium precisely because they feel they are receiving the "highest degree of attention and customization."\n\nIf we remove those formal service elements, how do you think that will affect our ability to command premium pricing for those large, profitable wedding events?\n\nSTUDENT: You are not a premium company so you shouldn\'t be commanding premium pricing. People reach out to Malwais because they love the pizza and the company image. They aren\'t expecting a fancy service. However, this will still make Malwais great money.\n\nCEO: I\'ll push back on that a bit, STUDENT. My background is in high-end food serviceFour Seasons, Ritz-Carlton. While the restaurant is \'fast casual,\' the catering arm has been positioned differently.\n\nThe case explicitly states that catering is the "most profitable part of the restaurant operation." This is largely because, as Evans notes, these events command premium pricing.\n\nIf we follow your advice and stop acting like a premium service for these formal events, what does that do to our most profitable business line?\n\nSTUDENT: time is up\n\nCEO: STUDENT, thank you for meeting with me. I am glad you were able to study this case and share your insights. I hope our conversation was challenging yet helpful. **Would you be willing to provide feedback by answering a few questions about our interaction?**\n\nSTUDENT: yes\n\nCEO: Great! On a scale of 1 to 5, how helpful was our conversation in your thinking through this case situation? (1=not helpful, 5=extremely helpful)\n\nSTUDENT: 5\n\nCEO: Thank you. What did you **like most** about this simulated conversation?\n\nSTUDENT: it gave me a new perspecitive on things!\n\nCEO: That\'s helpful. What way do you think this simulated conversation **might be improved**?\n\nSTUDENT: i thought it was great\n\nCEO: It has been a delight talking with you today. **Would you be willing to let me pass this conversation transcript to the developers to help improve the simulated conversations for future students?** The conversation will be completely anonymized (your name will be removed). This would be **a big help** in developing this AI chat case teaching tool .\n\nSTUDENT: yes\n\nCEO: Thank you for your time, STUDENT. Goodbye and have a nice day. I am going to turn this over to the AI Supervisor to give you feedback.') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE created_at=VALUES(created_at),student_id=VALUES(student_id),score=VALUES(score),summary=VALUES(summary),criteria=VALUES(criteria),persona=VALUES(persona),hints=VALUES(hints),helpful=VALUES(helpful),liked=VALUES(liked),improve=VALUES(improve),chat_model=VALUES(chat_model),super_model=VALUES(super_model),transcript=VALUES(transcript);
