 that the case explicitly attributed to catering. While his suggestion of social media advertising was a valid strategic pivot, he did not elaborate on how it would specifically replace the existing word-of-mouth mechanism mentioned in the case. The conversation ended without fully exploring these critical financial and strategic gaps.","question":"Did the student provide solid answers to chatbot questions?"},{"score":2,"feedback":"Joe used some isolated facts from the case, such as Evans\'s time spent on planning and the restaurant\'s operational metrics, to support his general claims about labor intensity and restaurant capacity. However, his core argument to abandon the catering business was not well-justified by the reading material, which instead positioned catering as a profitable segment with potential for scalability. Repeatedly stating that the case lacked sufficient information, while sometimes true for granular financial data, often served to avoid building a case-based justification for his main recommendations or reconciling them with existing facts.","question":"Did the student justify the answer using relevant reading information?"}]','sycophantic',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'gemini-2.5-flash','gemini-2.5-flash',NULL) ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE created_at=VALUES(created_at),student_id=VALUES(student_id),score=VALUES(score),summary=VALUES(summary),criteria=VALUES(criteria),persona=VALUES(persona),hints=VALUES(hints),helpful=VALUES(helpful),liked=VALUES(liked),improve=VALUES(improve),chat_model=VALUES(chat_model),super_model=VALUES(super_model),transcript=VALUES(transcript);
