business at the expense of the established restaurant. However, should you choose to keep the catering business, you should make that the greatest priority of the business. You can do this by hiring a separate catering team and investing in serious training with quality control evaluations of each of the operating catering franchisors.\n\nCEO: STUDENT, you\'ve brought up several new ideas herepop-ups, food trucks, hiring a dedicated team.\n\nThat\'s an interesting recommendation, but where in the case does it support that?\n\nSTUDENT: IT talks about the planning process being central to the case, it mentions that he wants to build a franchise, It doesn\'t mention Pop-ups, but this seems like a logical option if the company wants to retain the stability of a restaurant. I simply wanted to show that you can choose to do one of the operation styles very effectively, but it will be hard to do both unless you cede control and do it separately.\n\nCEO: I appreciate the creative thinking, STUDENT, but our strategy must be grounded in the facts and opportunities presented in the case document. We can\'t build a plan around hypothetical pop-ups.\n\nSo let\'s circle back to your original recommendation to eliminate catering. You haven\'t addressed my main concern: the case states catering is our most profitable operation. What is your plan, based *only on the information in the case*, to replace that high-margin revenue?\n\nSTUDENT: Time is up\n\nCEO: STUDENT, thank you for meeting with me. I am glad you were able to study this case and share your insights. I hope our conversation was challenging yet helpful. **Would you be willing to provide feedback by answering a few questions about our interaction?**\n\nSTUDENT: yes\n\nCEO: Great! On a scale of 1 to 5, how helpful was our conversation in your thinking through this case situation? (1=not helpful, 5=extremely helpful)\n\nSTUDENT: 2\n\nCEO: Thank you. What did you **like most** about this simulated conversation?\n\nSTUDENT: I like the interactivity\n\nCEO: That\'s helpful. What way do you think this simulated conversation **might be improved**?\n\nSTUDENT: I think it would be helpful if the consult-tee came with established questions and worked with you more like someone searching for specific advice. It could bring up information from the case to help prompt the reader if it has specific needs.\n\nCEO: It has been a delight talking with you today. **Would you be willing to let me pass this conversation transcript to the developers to help improve the simulated conversations for future students?** The conversation will be completely anonymized (your name will be removed). This would be **a big help** in developing this AI chat case teaching tool .\n\nSTUDENT: yes\n\nCEO: Thank you for your time, STUDENT. Goodbye and have a nice day. I am going to turn this over to the AI Supervisor to give you feedback.') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE created_at=VALUES(created_at),student_id=VALUES(student_id),score=VALUES(score),summary=VALUES(summary),criteria=VALUES(criteria),persona=VALUES(persona),hints=VALUES(hints),helpful=VALUES(helpful),liked=VALUES(liked),improve=VALUES(improve),chat_model=VALUES(chat_model),super_model=VALUES(super_model),transcript=VALUES(transcript);
